        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10064",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zend_framework",
                        "name": "zend_framework",
                        "displayName": "Zend Framework",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "05\/05\/06 08:41:33: Modified by php@dayclan.org\n\nI'm running ZF on IIS. It functions great with a small workaround. You have to install Isapi_Rewrite (http:\/\/www.isapirewrite.com\/) to get mod_rewrite-like functionality in IIS. Then in Zend_Controller_Router you only need to change line 52 in Zend\/Controller\/Router.php from\n\n$path = $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI'];\n\nto\n\n$path = strtolower($_SERVER['HTTP_X_REWRITE_URL']);\n\nIsapi_Rewrite sets the HTTP_X_REWRITE_URL $_SERVER variable to be what REQUEST_URI would be if you were running on Apache and using mod_rewrite.\n\nI hope that helps.\n06\/12\/06 06:22:42: Modified by Link",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zend_framework",
                        "name": "zend_framework",
                        "displayName": "Zend Framework",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-19T22:46:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-19T22:46:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10157",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=martel",
                        "name": "martel",
                        "displayName": "Michal Minicki",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could you provide working isapi rewrite rules? I'm trying those and they don't seem to work on my setup:\n\nRewriteCond     %{SCRIPT_FILENAME}      !-f\nRewriteCond     %{SCRIPT_FILENAME}      !-d\nRewriteRule ^.*$ index.php\n\nAnd this also doesn't work:\n\nRewriteRule !\\.(js|ico|gif|jpg|png|css|swf)$ index.php\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=martel",
                        "name": "martel",
                        "displayName": "Michal Minicki",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-23T10:30:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-23T10:30:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10177",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=martel",
                        "name": "martel",
                        "displayName": "Michal Minicki",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have found a working rewrite rule:\nRewriteRule (?!\\.(js|ico|gif|jpg|png|css|swf))$ index.php\n\nRouter works as expected. Without any changes to the code.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=martel",
                        "name": "martel",
